pullRequest.title: Avoid calling `toString()` when tracing Java dynamic proxies
pullRequest.bodyText:
This change will check if a parameter or object type is a proxy before tracing it.  If so, it will log "Proxy for " instead of invoking the toString() method - which could lead to unwanted behaviors in the associated invocation handler.
If the proxy instance implements other RAS-related interfaces, like Traceable, it will be traced according to those interfaces rather than as a proxy.
This change includes unit test changes.

nodes.bodyText:
This String does not make sense.  It does not give you the class of the object that is being proxied, so it would make more sense to me for it to just do the default toString() behavior:
className + "@" + Integer.toHexString(System.identityHashCode(objs))
This should return nullParamString not null
